sections.Soundtrack:
{{main|GoldenEye (soundtrack)}}
The soundtrack for GoldenEye was composed by French composer [[Éric Serra]] and released by EMI on November 14, 1995. The French composer composed and performed several synthesizer tracks, including the traditional opening sequence of the James Bond films. In a first for James Bond, the soundtrack composer himself performed his song in the closing credits (though not the first time for Eric Serra).

Serra's soundtrack for the movie remains a very divisive aspect of the movie; with one camp seeing it as giving the film an unique atmosphere that even elevates the film above the other Bond films,<ref>[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=zlTSB-7SmEM "The Bond Movie That Sounds Like NO Other" by The Nat Cave (@TheNatCav3)](Retrieved 07-04-2025)</ref> while others go as far as to say it is the single worst Bond movie soundtrack in the series' history.<ref>[https://www.filmtracks.com/titles/goldeneye.html Goldeneye (Eric Serra) - Filmtracks]</ref>

